Richard J. Bressler: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 7:43 AM ET
Media

Company Overview of iHeartMedia, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Richard J. Bressler  President, COO, CFO & Director, iHeartMedia, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 9 Board Members in 9 different organizations across 18 different industries.See Board Relationships60$3,453,809As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Richard J. Bressler, also known as Rich, has been the President and Chief Financial Officer at iHeartCommunications, Inc., CC Media Holdings, Inc., iHeartMedia, Inc. and iHeartMedia Capital I, LLC since July 29, 2013. Mr. Bressler has been the Chief Operating Officer of iHeartMedia, Inc., iHeartMedia Capital I, LLC and iHeartCommunications, Inc. since February 18, 2015. He has been Chief Financial Officer of Clear Channel Outdoor Holdings Inc. since July 29, 2013 ... and serves as its Chief Operating Officer. He serves as a Senior Advisor at Thomas H. Lee Partners, L.P. and previously served as its Managing Director. Mr. Bressler served as Executive Vice President at Time Warner Entertainment Company, L.P. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Time Warner Digital Media Fund since July 1999. He served as Executive Vice President of Historic TW Inc. since July 1999. He served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at Time Warner Inc. He joined CC Media Holdings on January 9, 2006. He served as a Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at Viacom Inc., (alternate name CBS Corporation) from May 2001 to 2005, with responsibility for managing all of Viacom's strategic, financial, business development and technology functions. He served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at AOL Time Warner I nc. from March 1995 to June 1999. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at AOL Time Warner Investments (now known as Time Warner Investments). He served as Vice President of TWI Cable Inc. He joined Time Warner Inc. in 1988. Prior to that, he was a Partner at Ernst & Young since, 1979. He served as the Chairman of Center for Communication, Inc. He has been a Director of iHeartMedia, Inc. since May 2007. He serves as a Director of iHeartCommunications, Inc., The Nielsen Company B.V., Nielsen Finance Co., and Nielsen Finance LLC. He serves as Manager of iHeartMedia Capital I, LLC. He serves as a Member of National Advisory Board of J.P. Morgan Chase National. He serves as Member of Advisory Board at Brooklyn Sports & Entertainment, LLC. Mr. Bressler has been the Director of CC Media Holdings, Inc., since May 2007 since January 2011. He has been an Independent Director of Gartner Consulting, Inc. and Gartner Inc. since February 2006. He is a Board Observer of Univision Communications, Inc. He serves as a Trustee of the New School. He served as a Member of the Supervisory Board at Nielsen Holdings plc since July 28, 2006. He served as a Director of BB Liquidating Inc. from May 2001 to October 16, 2004 and Time Warner Digital Media Fund. He served as a Director of Center for Communication, Inc. He served as a Director of Time Warner Entertainment Company, L.P. Mr. Bressler served as a Director of Warner Music Group Corp., since May 10, 2005. He served as a Director of Nielsen Holdings plc from January 2011 to December 19, 2013. He served as Director of American Media Operations, Inc. and American Media Inc., from March 15, 2006 to January 30, 2009. He served as a Director of Univision Communications Inc., until October 17, 2007. He is on the Board of Visitors of the Fuqua School of Business at Duke University and the Dean's Council of Columbia University's School of the Arts. Mr. Bressler holds a BBA degree in Accounting from Adelphi University.Read Full Background




